          <name xml:lang="en">carbon content, fossil</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">dimensionless</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">n-olefins in detergent context is produced from paraffin and/or ethylene, and it's considered a C10-C16 molecule with at least one double bound (ecoinvent v2.2 report n12, pg 10). C13 was used, as average, and 3 double bonds were stated, so the formula used is C13H22.</comment>
        </property>
